    "updated_at": "2014-10-25T16:35:44Z",
    "body": "Kernels will of course have to supply their own version of the failure function, which should be something like linux's panic. I was worried about libraries, which don't want to export a non-weak `stack_exhausted` etc. symbols (as these will conflict with symbols with the same name from other libraries).\n",
